# Clipboard configuration

## What I want
Selected text goes to PRIMARY
Copied text go to CLIPBOARD

Shortcuts
  copy  (except in terminal)  --> Ctrl + C
  copy  (in-terminal)         --> Ctrl + Shift + C
  paste (except in terminal)  --> Ctrl + V
  paste (in-terminal)         --> Ctrl + Shift + V
  erase PRIMARY and CLIPBOARD --> ?
  copy PRIMARY to CLIPBOARD   --> windows+`

## Xorg
### Using xsel
erase PRIMARY # I don't think we can erase PRIMARY, because it is fetched from another window
erase CLIPBOARD
```
# Short version
xsel -b -c
# Long version
xsel --clipboard --clear
```
copy PRIMARY to CLIPBOARD
```
# Short version
xsel -p | xsel -b
# Long version
xsel --primary | xsel --clipboard
```
